def _escape(text: str) -> str:
    replacements = {
        "\\": r"\textbackslash{}",
        "&": r"\&",
        "%": r"\%",
        "$": r"\$",
        "#": r"\#",
        "_": r"\_",
        "{": r"\{",
        "}": r"\}",
        "~": r"\textasciitilde{}",
        "^": r"\textasciicircum{}",
    }
    return "".join(replacements.get(ch, ch) for ch in text)


def _render() -> str:
    total_topics = sum(len(entries) for _, _, entries in _SECTIONS)
    lines: list[str] = [
        r"\documentclass[11pt,openany]{book}",
        r"\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}",
        r"\usepackage[T1]{fontenc}",
        r"\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}",
        r"\usepackage{hyperref}",
        r"\usepackage{enumitem}",
        r"\usepackage{parskip}",
        r"\setcounter{secnumdepth}{0}",
        r"\setcounter{tocdepth}{0}",
        r"\hypersetup{colorlinks=true,linkcolor=blue,urlcolor=blue}",
        r"\begin{document}",
        rf"\title{{Two Hundred Questions in Formal Methods: Traditional Approaches and Deppy's Analogues}}",
        r"\author{Generated for the deppy repository}",
        r"\date{\today}",
        r"\maketitle",
        r"\tableofcontents",
        r"\chapter*{Preface}",
        r"\addcontentsline{toc}{chapter}{Preface}",
        rf"This document is an incremental catalogue of {total_topics} comparisons between basic formal-methods topics and deppy's sheaf-cohomological approach.",
        r"For each topic, the document gives three things: the traditional method in its own terms, the closest honest deppy analogue, and a relationship label that says whether the comparison is best read as a generalization, a direct instance, an asymptotic improvement, an orthogonal complement, or only a partial analogue.",
        r"",
        r"The goal is not to force every topic into the same mold. In some places deppy is clearly a direct reframing, as with obstruction-style bug detection and cover-relative equivalence. In others it is better understood as a manager of heterogeneous evidence, or as a retrofit semantic checker that is weaker than construction-time type disciplines but broader in applicability to ordinary Python.",
        r"",
        r"The recurring deppy idea is this: local facts live at observation sites, restriction maps transport them, globally consistent families form zero-th cohomology, and irreducible failures of local-to-global composition appear as first-cohomology obstructions. That perspective is sometimes a strict extension of traditional machinery, sometimes merely a compatible overlay, and occasionally not yet the right tool at all.",
    ]

    topic_index = 1
    for title, intro, entries in _SECTIONS:
        lines.extend(
            [
                "",
                rf"\chapter{{{_escape(title)}}}",
                _escape(intro),
            ]
        )
        for item in entries:
            lines.extend(
                [
                    "",
                    rf"\section*{{{topic_index}. {_escape(item['question'])}}}",
                    rf"\textbf{{Traditional approach.}} {_escape(item['traditional'])}",
                    "",
                    rf"\textbf{{Deppy analogue.}} {_escape(item['deppy'])}",
                    "",
                    rf"\textbf{{Relationship.}} {_escape(item['relation'])}",
                ]
            )
            topic_index += 1

    lines.extend(
        [
            "",
            r"\chapter*{Closing note}",
            r"\addcontentsline{toc}{chapter}{Closing note}",
            r"The most useful way to read the catalogue is not as a claim that deppy replaces the entire formal-methods ecosystem. Its strongest identity is as a local-to-global organizer: it absorbs contracts, solver results, proof artifacts, runtime evidence, and semantic judgments into a common object, then uses gluing and obstruction theory to say what still does not fit.",
            r"",
            r"That is why some comparisons in the document are marked as strict generalizations, others as partial analogues, and others as orthogonal. The point of being wise about the analogue is exactly to preserve those distinctions.",
            r"\end{document}",
        ]
    )
    return "\n".join(lines) + "\n"


if __name__ == "__main__":
    _OUTPUT.write_text(_render(), encoding="utf-8")
